table:table-cell.text:p: These tables are published as part of the 'Offender Management Statistics Quarterly' publication by the Ministry of Justice.

text:p.text:a: Link to 'Offender Management Statistics Quarterly' (opens in a new window)

table:table-cell.text:p: Further details of the terminology used to report prison population statistics can be found in the definitions section for population in the 'Guide to Offender Management Statistics' published alongside these tables.
All tables are for England and Wales.
The majority of the figures in these tables are drawn from the Prison National Offender Management Information System (Prison NOMIS). Any additional data sources are listed above the relevant tables.
The figures in these tables have been drawn from administrative IT systems which, as with any large-scale recording system, are subject to possible errors with data entry and processing.

Occasionally we identify issues with previously published figures. Revised figures will be marked with [rev]. A revised marker in a column heading indicates that some or all of the values in that column have been updated.
Data quality improvement work in 2023 to 2025 may have resulted in small unmarked changes to previously published figures.
A [z] symbol has been used in cases with one (or both) comparator value(s) less than 50.
Some tables refer to notes. When notes are mentioned, the note marker is presented in square brackets. The note text can be found in the 'Notes' table.

Where necessary, [c] has been used to suppress values of one or two to prevent the disclosure of individual information. Further disclosure control may be completed where this alone is not sufficient. This could include the secondary suppression of zero values. Disclosure control is also applied to breakdowns by prison for any prison with a population of fewer than 100.
This release was published on Thursday 29 January 2026 at 9:30am, and covers prison population data as at 31 December 2025.
The next quarterly release will be published on Thursday 30 April 2026 at 9:30am, and will cover prison population data as at 31 March 2026.
Offender Management Statistics Quarterly is released every three months on the last working Thursday of January, April, July, and October.
Information about establishment predominant function and designation is published by HM Prison and Probation Service in 'Prisons and their resettlement providers'.

As part of wider ongoing data improvement work, and following consultation with operational colleagues, the prisoner religion / belief codes have been streamlined to facilitate more accurate data entry and initial processing. These changes occured in June 2025 and and resulted in a number of prisoners moving between religion / belief groups. Therefore, figures before 30 June 2025 are not fully consistent with or comparable to figures for or after 30 June 2025.
Life (all variations) includes mandatory, discretionary, and automatic life sentences as well as those relating to young adults and juveniles held in prison custody.
'Tariff not recorded' includes cases where a confirmed tariff expiry date has yet to be received, and any unmatched records.
Excludes 'Tariff not recorded' records. These can be found in table 1.Q.15.
Tariff length is the time between date of sentencing and tariff expiry date, and does not take into account any time served on remand.

The figures for Secure Children's Homes and Secure Training Centres may not match the monthly custody figures within the 'Youth custody data' publication (link on the cover page). This is due to different methodologies and snapshot dates.
